# Build and run

When the user asks to run, build, start, or "build and run" the app:

- **Always use port 3000.** Do not start the app on other ports (3001, 3005, 3010, etc.). If port 3000 is in use, kill the process on 3000 first (e.g. `lsof -ti :3000 | xargs kill -9`), then start.
- Use **`npm start`** as the default command. It runs `npm run build && next start`, so the app is always built for production and then started on port 3000.
- To start without rebuilding (e.g. after a previous build), use `npm run start:server` (also on port 3000).

Do not run only `next start` or only `next build` when the intent is to run the app; use `npm start` so build happens automatically.
